    "client_msg_id": "cf73d80f-c5d8-4e54-a1bc-e00ed5055f4e",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "And if you  know category theory, then you already know what compilation is: it's just some kind of functor from one category (language) to another :stuck_out_tongue:. Compiler textbooks spend a lot of time talking about stuff like parsing and lexing, which is a trivial and unenlightening side-effect of demanding that our programs be serialised as text strings and manipulated as syntax _trees_ (which I encourage people to challenge).",
